Why Lists Are Useful
You can:
Access any item by its position (index)
Add or remove items
Loop through them
Store any number of values in one variable

a=[2,5,7,8,4]
l=len(a)
b=0

for i in range(l):
    print (a[i])
    b+=a[i]
print(b)
    
