ðŸ§  Task 3: Filter Even Numbers from a List
Instructions:
Create a list of numbers (example: [10, 23, 45, 6, 28, 55, 70]).
Use a loop to filter even numbers from the list.
Store the even numbers in a new list.
Print the new list.

    A=[10, 23, 45, 6, 28, 55, 70]
    Even=[]
    l=len(A)
    for i in range(0,l):
        if A[i]%2==0:
            Even.append(A[i])
    print(Even)
    
